HOUSE RESOLUTION 183
By Miller
A RESOLUTION to commend David Brisco for exemplary service
as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, we are pleased to recognize certain persons who
have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, David Brisco is one such individual, who has distinguished himself in his
role as a legislative intern for Representative Larry Miller; Mr. Brisco's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators he assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Brisco is originally from Chicago, Illinois, where he grew up with his
father, Stephen, Sr.; his mother, Angela; and his brothers, Stephen, Jr., and Jason; and
WHEREAS, David Brisco is a senior at Tennessee State University (TSU), where he is
highly regarded by his peers; and
WHEREAS, he has achieved academic success while majoring in criminal justice with a
minor in political science and playing in the Aristocrat of Bands, TSU's Grammy-award-winning
marching band; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Brisco is deeply passionate about law, public advocacy, and the
criminal justice system; and
WHEREAS, his favorite pastimes include photography, watching movies, exploring new
foods, and listening to and playing music; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize himself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further his studies, Mr. Brisco brought his many abilities
and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth
General Assembly; and
HR0183
017038
- 1 -

WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Mr. Brisco has surpassed all
criteria that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, David Brisco has performed his many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby
commend David Brisco for outstanding service as a legislative intern for Representative Larry
Miller and extend to him our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
